The total number of words is 74.

2. Counting the number of long words:
Long words are kemikalierna (10), konsekvensen (10), övergödda (8), ekologiskt (10), kemikalier (10), överallt (8), samma (5) (not a long word), sorts (5) (not a long word), klimat (6) (not a long word),/Dk genmodifierar (11), växternas (9), egenskaper (11). These words 10, or with at least 8 letters.

The total number of long words is actually 11, but using some other common heuristics, Swedish uses a value of 7. But to create this model, another set of words, i. e the complex words need to be determined.

We will require to perform a count of these on the heuristics provided after counting the words, and those two numbers that you now must combine to complete the readability algorithm computation.

The number of long words was determined when we counted our set of “long words”  and the final number required for the LIX heuristics, and also determined the character count so that we can compute the mean size of words now (den komplexe mått på ord). We need for LIX the  numbers for 

a = 100 x the total number of words containing more than 8 characters 
b = the total number of words
c = the average number of the character count for each of the words.

 3:   a = 11
b  = 74  : 74 is the number of words.
For  counting,   c = (total letters)/(number of words)  dvs 325/74 ≈ 4.39
Therefore LIX = a + b/c 
Thus: 
LIX = 11 + 74/4.39
LIX = 11 + 16.85 ≈ 27.85